## What each new piece does

| Class | Role |
|---|---|
| `TextStyleAnalyzer` | Splits pixels into light/dark clusters → extracts bg colour, text colour, font size estimate |
| `NaturalTextBillboard` | Paints bg colour to erase original → edge-fades to blend → draws translation in matched style |
| Updated `ARTextRenderer` | Passes style into billboard creation, stores per-block styles |
| Updated `MainActivity` | Runs style analysis per block right after detection, passes to renderer |

---

## The visual pipeline per text block

```
Detected text block region (pixels from PixelCopy)
        ↓
TextStyleAnalyzer.analyze()
  → border strip sampled → clean background colour
  → pixel cluster split  → text colour
  → line count ÷ height  → font size estimate
        ↓
NaturalTextBillboard.create()
  → fill rect with background colour  (original text gone)
  → edge gradient fade                (blends with real scene)
  → draw translated text              (same colour, same size)
        ↓
Uploaded as GL texture → rendered as billboard in AR
  → sticks to real surface
  → always faces camera
  → looks like the translation was printed there originally
```